remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoder` provides static methods for encoding pixel data to the WebP
image format. Both lossy and lossless encoding are supported via
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderOptions>. The encoder also supports creating
animated WebP files from a sequence of <xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderFrame>
instances.

This is a static class with no state and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
using var pixmap = bitmap.PeekPixels();
var options = new SKWebpEncoderOptions(SKWebpEncoderCompression.Lossy, 80);
using var data = SKWebpEncoder.Encode(pixmap, options);
if (data is null)
    throw new InvalidOperationException("Encoding failed.");
File.WriteAllBytes("output.webp", data.ToArray());
```
